4.1 Starting transcription from Emacs
=====================================

Two commands launch transcription:

   • ‘M-x eve-transcribe’ prompts for a directory, scans for media
     files, and starts ‘eve transcribe’ asynchronously.  On success the
     manifest opens automatically in eve-mode.

   • ‘M-x eve-dired-transcribe’ runs from Dired using the marked files
     (or the file at point when nothing is marked).

   On failure, the ‘*eve transcribe*’ buffer appears so you can inspect
the error output.


File: eve.info,  Node: Backends,  Next: Configuration,  Prev: Starting transcription from Emacs,  Up: Transcription

4.2 Backends
============

‘eve transcribe’ supports three backends:

Backend            Flag                         Notes
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
‘faster-whisper’   ‘--backend faster-whisper’   Default.  Fast, local, good accuracy.
‘transformers’     ‘--backend transformers’     HuggingFace models.  Needs optional deps.
‘nemo’             ‘--backend nemo’             NVIDIA NeMo.  Needs optional deps.

   The ‘--verbatim’ flag (on by default in Emacs) biases
‘faster-whisper’ toward preserving disfluencies and filler words.  For
‘transformers’ and ‘nemo’, choose a verbatim-friendly model instead.

   Good starting points:
   • ‘transformers’: ‘nyrahealth/CrisperWhisper’
   • ‘nemo’: ‘nvidia/parakeet-ctc-1.1b’


File: eve.info,  Node: Configuration,  Next: Installing optional backends,  Prev: Backends,  Up: Transcription

4.3 Configuration
=================

Variable                       Default               Description
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
‘eve-transcribe-backend’       ‘"faster-whisper"’    Backend name passed to ‘eve transcribe’.
‘eve-transcribe-model’         ‘"medium.en"’         Model identifier.
‘eve-transcribe-verbatim’      ‘t’                   Pass ‘--verbatim’ to the backend.
‘eve-transcribe-tag-fillers’   ‘t’                   Tag filler words during transcription.
‘eve-media-extensions’         ‘("mp4" "mov" ...)’   File types scanned by ‘eve-transcribe’.


File: eve.info,  Node: Installing optional backends,  Prev: Configuration,  Up: Transcription

4.4 Installing optional backends
================================

The ‘transformers’ and ‘nemo’ backends need extra Python dependencies.
From the repository root:

     uv sync --project cli --extra transformers
     # or
     uv sync --project cli --extra nemo

   Or from ‘cli/’:

     uv pip install .[transformers]
     uv pip install .[nemo]


