File: eve.info,  Node: Concept,  Next: Configuration (1),  Up: Filler Words

6.1 Concept
===========

Filler words ("um", "uh", "you know") clutter transcripts.  Eve's filler
workflow is non-destructive: words are _tagged_ as fillers first, then
_optionally deleted_.  Tagged fillers are highlighted in the buffer with
a distinct face and excluded from compilation.  You can untag them at
any time.


File: eve.info,  Node: Configuration (1),  Next: Commands,  Prev: Concept,  Up: Filler Words

6.2 Configuration
=================

     ;; Plain strings — single words or multi-word phrases
     (setq eve-filler-phrases '("um" "uh" "you know" "to be honest with you"))

   ‘eve-filler-phrases’ stores phrases as plain strings.  Matching is
case-insensitive and ignores punctuation.  The list is persisted when
you use the interactive add commands.

   The legacy ‘eve-filler-regex’ variable is still honoured for
backwards compatibility but ‘eve-filler-phrases’ is preferred.


File: eve.info,  Node: Commands,  Next: Auto-tagging on file open,  Prev: Configuration (1),  Up: Filler Words

6.3 Commands
============

Key         Command                         Description
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
‘f’         ‘eve-dwim-filler’               Add the word at point to phrases and retag; or delete region as filler.
‘F’         ‘eve-delete-fillers’            Mark all tagged fillers as deleted.
‘C-c C-d’   ‘eve-delete-fillers’            Same as ‘F’ from the ‘C-c’ prefix map.
—           ‘M-x eve-tag-fillers’           Tag all matching words in the buffer.
—           ‘M-x eve-add-filler-at-point’   Add the word at point to ‘eve-filler-phrases’ and retag.
—           ‘M-x eve-add-filler-region’     Add the selected phrase to ‘eve-filler-phrases’ and retag.


File: eve.info,  Node: Auto-tagging on file open,  Prev: Commands,  Up: Filler Words

6.4 Auto-tagging on file open
=============================

Fillers are tagged automatically every time a TJM manifest is opened.
If you add a new phrase to ‘eve-filler-phrases’, reopen the file or run
‘M-x eve-tag-fillers’ to apply the updated list.


