File: eve.info,  Node: Concept (1),  Next: Editing b-roll metadata,  Up: B-Roll

7.1 Concept
===========

B-roll is supplementary footage that plays over (or instead of) the main
recording.  Eve supports three compositing modes:

   • *Replace* (default) — the b-roll clip completely replaces the
     source video for the duration of the segment.  The source audio is
     kept unless you change the audio policy.

   • *Pip* (picture-in-picture) — the b-roll is scaled down and
     composited on top of the source video.  You control position and
     size.

   • *Overlay* — alias for replace.  Treated identically by the
     renderer.


File: eve.info,  Node: Editing b-roll metadata,  Next: Compositing modes in detail,  Prev: Concept (1),  Up: B-Roll

7.2 Editing b-roll metadata
===========================

Press ‘b’ (‘eve-edit-broll’) on a segment to set or modify its b-roll.
The command prompts for each field in turn:

Field            Prompt                              Description
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
‘file’           "B-roll file"                       Path to a video, image, or ‘.json’ template.  Blank clears the b-roll.
‘mode’           "Mode (overlay/replace/pip)"        Compositing mode (see above).
‘audio’          "Audio (source/mute/broll)"         Which audio track the rendered segment uses.
‘start_offset’   "Start offset (MM:SS or seconds)"   Where to begin playback in the b-roll clip.
‘duration’       "Duration (MM:SS or seconds)"       How long the b-roll plays; blank uses the segment duration.
‘still’          "Treat as still image?"             Auto-detected for ‘.png’, ‘.jpg’, etc.  Loops the image for the segment.
‘continue’       "Continue from previous?"           Part of a continuation chain (see below).

   Additional keys:

Key         Command                         Description
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
‘B’         ‘eve-toggle-broll-continue’     Copy b-roll from the previous segment and mark as continuation.
‘C-c C-b’   ‘eve-edit-broll-placeholders’   Edit placeholder values for the current segment.

   B-roll metadata is stored in the segment's ‘edit.broll’ field in the
JSON manifest.


File: eve.info,  Node: Compositing modes in detail,  Next: Audio policy,  Prev: Editing b-roll metadata,  Up: B-Roll

7.3 Compositing modes in detail
===============================

* Menu:

* Replace mode::
* Pip mode::


File: eve.info,  Node: Replace mode,  Next: Pip mode,  Up: Compositing modes in detail

7.3.1 Replace mode
------------------

The b-roll video replaces the source video entirely.  The renderer trims
the b-roll to the segment's duration, starting at ‘start_offset’.  If
the b-roll is shorter than the segment, it is extended to fit.

   When ‘still’ is true, the image is looped for the full segment
duration using ‘ffmpeg -loop 1’.


File: eve.info,  Node: Pip mode,  Prev: Replace mode,  Up: Compositing modes in detail

7.3.2 Pip mode
--------------

The b-roll is scaled and positioned as an inset window over the source.
Position and size are controlled by a ‘position’ object in the JSON:

     {
       "file": "demo-recording.mp4",
       "mode": "pip",
       "position": {
         "x": 0.05,
         "y": 0.05,
         "width": 0.3
       }
     }

Field     Default   Description
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
‘x’       ‘0.05’    Horizontal offset as a fraction of the main video width (0.0-1.0).
‘y’       ‘0.05’    Vertical offset as a fraction of the main video height (0.0-1.0).
‘width’   ‘0.3’     Width of the pip window as a fraction of the main video width.

   The height is calculated automatically to preserve the b-roll's
aspect ratio.


File: eve.info,  Node: Audio policy,  Next: JSON templates,  Prev: Compositing modes in detail,  Up: B-Roll

7.4 Audio policy
================

Each b-roll entry has an ‘audio’ field that controls which audio track
appears in the rendered segment:

   • ‘source’ (default) — keep the original recording's audio.
   • ‘broll’ — use the audio track from the b-roll clip.  Not available
     for still images.
   • ‘mute’ — no audio for this segment.


File: eve.info,  Node: JSON templates,  Next: Placeholders without templates,  Prev: Audio policy,  Up: B-Roll

7.5 JSON templates
==================

When the ‘file’ field points to a ‘.json’ file instead of a media file,
eve treats it as a *template*.  The template JSON has this structure:

     {
       "template": "lower-third.png",
       "overlays": [
         {
           "placeholder": "SPEAKER_NAME",
           "fontsize": 36,
           "color": "white",
           "x": 80,
           "y": 620,
           "boxColor": "black@0.6"
         },
         {
           "placeholder": "SPEAKER_TITLE",
           "fontsize": 24,
           "color": "#cccccc",
           "x": 80,
           "y": 665
         }
       ],
       "placeholders": {
         "SPEAKER_NAME": "Full Name",
         "SPEAKER_TITLE": "Job Title"
       }
     }

   • ‘template’ — path to the actual media file (image or video).
   • ‘overlays’ — a list of text overlays rendered with ffmpeg
     ‘drawtext’.  Each overlay references a ‘placeholder’ key by name.
   • ‘placeholders’ — default values for each placeholder.
     Segment-level overrides (set via ‘C-c C-b’) take precedence.

* Menu:

* Overlay fields::
