9.5 Video layout
================

Set ‘eve-video-layout’ to ‘t’ to arrange the screen for editing: Emacs
takes the bottom portion of the display and mpv sits directly above it —
borderless, always-on-top, with automatic letterboxing.

     (setq eve-video-layout t)

     ;; Fraction of screen height for the video window (default 0.6 = 60%)
     (setq eve-video-layout-ratio 0.6)

   The layout activates on the first play command and the original frame
geometry is restored when playback stops.  Skipped when Emacs is in
macOS native fullscreen.

   Configuration:

