10.1 Timestamp ruler
====================

‘eve-ruler-mode’ (active by default) displays ‘[hh:mm:ss]’ markers in
the right margin.  Each marker is placed next to the segment that
_reaches_ that milestone in the rendered video — deleted content is
excluded from the running total.

   The total rendered duration appears in the mode line.

     ;; Change the milestone interval (default 30 seconds)
     (setq eve-ruler-interval 60.0)

   Toggle the ruler with ‘C-c C-l’ (‘eve-ruler-mode’).


File: eve.info,  Node: Hiding deleted segments,  Next: Word-level display,  Prev: Timestamp ruler,  Up: Display

10.2 Hiding deleted segments
============================

‘C-c C-h’ (‘eve-hide-deleted-mode’) toggles visibility of deleted words
and segments.  When active (the default), deleted content is hidden and
the transcript reads as it will render.  When inactive, deleted content
appears with a strikethrough face.


File: eve.info,  Node: Word-level display,  Prev: Hiding deleted segments,  Up: Display

10.3 Word-level display
=======================

‘C-c C-w’ (‘eve-toggle-words’) shows or hides per-word timing
annotations under each segment.  Useful when inspecting or adjusting
precise cut points.

